<b>BBBike</b> is an information system for cyclists in Berlin and
Brandenburg (Germany). The application has the following features:
<ul>
 <li>Display map with streets, cycle paths, bad surfaces, railways,
 rivers, parks, altitudes and other map features
 <li>Find routes between two points. The route-finder may be
 customized to match cyclists preferences, amongst others:
 <ul>
  <li>fastest route
  <li>avoid busy streets
  <li>avoid bad surfaces, for example cobblestones
  <li>prefer "green" routes (in parks, forest or along rivers and lakes)
  <li>consider current wind direction and strength and hills
 </ul>
 <li>Current road works in Berlin are known and used in route calculations
 <li>Output map with route as PDF or a GPS track
 <li>A bike power calculator
 <li>Automatically fetch current Berlin weather data
</ul>
<p>

<a href="screenshots.en.html">Screenshots</a> of
the desktop application which is available for Linux, Unix,
Mac&#160;OS&#160;X, and Windows.

